                                    OOP (Object Oriented Programming)

    - OOP in java is a programming paradigm which is based on concept of class and object.
    - OOP enables modularity, reusability, and provides better code structure.
    - Java is fully object oriented langugage with primitive data types as the exception.

    The Principles of Object Oriented Programming are/ Pillars of OOP:
            1) Class
            2) Object
            3) Inheritance
            4) Polymorphism
            5) Encapsulation
            6) Abstraction

    
